text: Partecosta trilineata is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Terebridae, the auger snails.MolluscaBase eds. (2020). MolluscaBase. Partecosta trilineata (Bozzetti, 2008). Accessed through: World Register of Marine Species at: http://www.marinespecies.org/aphia.php?p=taxdetails&id;=1415441 on 2020-01-28 ==Distribution== This marine species occurs off Southern Madagascar. ==References== * Bozzetti L.
